column1: Table S1: Weather data collected from Racetrack Playa, Death Valley National Park
The weather station was equipped with Campbell Scientific CR-800 Data Logger, CS LI200X-LC Pyranometer, CS HMP35C-LC Temp and RH probe, CS GPS16X-HVS-PW, and a R.M. Young 05103-5 Wind Monitor.
Rainfall collection was made with a Campbell Scientific TE525-LC Tipping Bucket Rain Gauge
Records of Rainfall, Insolation, Air temperature, and Wind velocity are all hourly averages with the time stamp given in the first column
The record of Maximum wind gust strength (in column 7) is calculated to the nearest minute with a time stamp given in Column 6
